Inflation Re-Emerging as a ‘Key Concern’ for Africa, IMF Says

-- B y   S a r a h   M c G r e g o r
-- 
2011-10-19T06:33:21Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-10-19/inflation-re-emerging-as-a-key-concern-for-africa-imf-says.html
Inflation is re-emerging as a “key
concern” in  Africa  and there’s now more of a need for strong
economic management on the continent than there was a year ago,
Ragnar Gudmundsson, the IMF’s representative in  Kenya , told
reporters today in Nairobi, the capital.  To contact the reporter on this story:
